 Committees are sometimes asked to address issues that come up in the full board meetings but that need more research. The committees then make recommendations to the full board. Committee members are appointed by the board president. The IRE board of directors revamped IRE*s committee structure at an April retreat in Missouri, aimed at improving communication and encouraging more membership participation in the organization. Shawn McIntosh, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution David Boardman, The Seattle Times Duane Pohlman, WEWS-Cleveland Stephen C. Miller, The New York Times Development Committee - Oversees fund-raising. 